            "detailed_description": "We aim to provide the most immersive and enjoyable representation of strategic 21st-century combat possible on the PC. <i>Modern Combat</i> caters to newcomers and veterans alike, and incorporates both traditional and 'Hardcore' damage systems.<br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>Free Modification</strong> - Download and play at no cost whatsoever!<br><br></li><li><strong>New Setting</strong> - Make the transition from 1940s Europe to current-day China. All-new factions, artwork, maps, effects and music help to bring a near-future Sino-American war to life.<br><br></li><li><strong>Modern Warfare</strong> - Deploy helicopters, infantry fighting vehicles, MLRS trucks and digital reconnaissance vehicles. Fight the enemy with guided missiles, remote-controlled machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, suppressors, thermal goggles, ghillie suits, targeting lasers and more.<br><br></li><li><strong>Faithful CoH Gameplay</strong> - A new spin on familiar Victory Point and Annihilate multiplayer game-modes with all the strategic depth that CoH has to offer. Try our Hardcore modes for more realism, or our custom campaign mission for a new singleplayer experience.<br><br></li><li><strong>Competitive Focus</strong> - Designed with high-level competition in mind, Modern Combat strives for multiplayer balance.<br><br></li><li><strong>Communal Roots</strong> - Driven by community feedback and funded entirely by community donations, Modern Combat is a project by players, for players. Visit our forums to provide feedback, and join our Steam group to meet fellow players.</li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><strong>Rework</strong></h2> <br><br>Development is ongoing, with a mod overhaul currently in the works... stay tuned for more info!<h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><strong>Known Issues</strong></h2> <br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>To avoid game-breaking bugs, players must own all four CoH factions. <br><br></li><li>When loading a saved game, certain mod assets (such as weapons) may not load correctly.<br><br></li><li>Both US and Chinese troops employ existing US voice files. This is unfortunate (and immersion-breaking), but something we're currently unable to improve.</li></ul>",
            "about_the_game": "We aim to provide the most immersive and enjoyable representation of strategic 21st-century combat possible on the PC. <i>Modern Combat</i> caters to newcomers and veterans alike, and incorporates both traditional and 'Hardcore' damage systems.<br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>Free Modification</strong> - Download and play at no cost whatsoever!<br><br></li><li><strong>New Setting</strong> - Make the transition from 1940s Europe to current-day China. All-new factions, artwork, maps, effects and music help to bring a near-future Sino-American war to life.<br><br></li><li><strong>Modern Warfare</strong> - Deploy helicopters, infantry fighting vehicles, MLRS trucks and digital reconnaissance vehicles. Fight the enemy with guided missiles, remote-controlled machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, suppressors, thermal goggles, ghillie suits, targeting lasers and more.<br><br></li><li><strong>Faithful CoH Gameplay</strong> - A new spin on familiar Victory Point and Annihilate multiplayer game-modes with all the strategic depth that CoH has to offer. Try our Hardcore modes for more realism, or our custom campaign mission for a new singleplayer experience.<br><br></li><li><strong>Competitive Focus</strong> - Designed with high-level competition in mind, Modern Combat strives for multiplayer balance.<br><br></li><li><strong>Communal Roots</strong> - Driven by community feedback and funded entirely by community donations, Modern Combat is a project by players, for players. Visit our forums to provide feedback, and join our Steam group to meet fellow players.</li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><strong>Rework</strong></h2> <br><br>Development is ongoing, with a mod overhaul currently in the works... stay tuned for more info!<h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><strong>Known Issues</strong></h2> <br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>To avoid game-breaking bugs, players must own all four CoH factions. <br><br></li><li>When loading a saved game, certain mod assets (such as weapons) may not load correctly.<br><br></li><li>Both US and Chinese troops employ existing US voice files. This is unfortunate (and immersion-breaking), but something we're currently unable to improve.</li></ul>",
